{"questionId":"22443537","questionHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;Show that the area, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the carpet can be expressed as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to combine area formulas to express <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct substitution for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> and expansion of brackets&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The <em><strong>AG</strong></em> line must be stated for the final <strong><em>A1</em></strong> to be awarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22443537","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.12b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the area, A m2, of the carpet can be expressed as A=10x-πx24.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Prior learning","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—The circle, arc and area of sector, degrees only"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}